HEADWORD: Established suit
<hw>Es*tab"lished suit</hw>. <fld>(Contract bridge, Whist)</fld> <def>A
plain suit in which a player (or side) could, except for trumping, take
tricks with all his remaining cards.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

